$k = random(2,3,1);
$v4 = 16-4*$k;

$checkbox_mc = new_checkbox_multiple_choice();
$checkbox_mc -> qa("What is the meaning of the quantity \( v(4) \) ?  Select all that apply if more than one statement is correct.",
        "The object's velocity in 4 seconds.");
$checkbox_mc -> extra("How much the object has moved in 4 seconds.",
                      "The object's velocity in 4 hours.",
                      "In how many hours will the velocity be 4 ft/sec.",
                      "In how seconds will the object have moved 4 ft.",
                      "The average velocity of the object over the 4 second 
                       interval.");
$checkbox_mc -> makeLast("None of the above");

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 34:
$BR $SPACE $BR
Let $SPACE \( v(t) = t^2 - $k t \) $SPACE be the velocity, in feet per second, of an object at time $BITALIC t${EITALIC}, in seconds.
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
a) What is the initial velocity? $SPACE \{ ans_rule(10) \} ft/sec
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
b) When does the object have a velocity of zero?  If there is more than time, list all answers in a comma separated list. $SPACE $SPACE \{ ans_rule(10) \} seconds
$BR $SPACE $BR
c) \{ $checkbox_mc -> print_q \}
$BR
\{ $checkbox_mc -> print_a \}

END_TEXT

ANS( num_cmp(0) );
ANS( number_list_cmp( "0, $k" ) );
ANS(checkbox_cmp( $checkbox_mc -> correct_ans ));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
a)  The initial velocity at time \( t = 0 \) is \( v(0) = 0^2 - $k(0) = 0 \ \mbox{ft/s} \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) Solving \( 0 = t^2 - $k t = t(t-$k) \) when \( t = 0 \ \) seconds and \( t = $k \ \) seconds.
$BR $SPACE $BR
c) \( v(4) \) tells us the object's velocity after 4 seconds.
$BR
END_SOLUTION
      
